reviews.review_text: so much energy this is one of the best shows ive heard in a while. there is so much energy in jerrys solos, and donna gets to sing a song too. stagger lee, shakedown, and estimated prophet are some highlights.

must've been great agreed...lots of energy here.  i wish it was a better recording...or should i say, i wish it was a sbd.  however, that could just be personal preference...if you like auds, then you will love this show.

potentially worth the dl just for the shakedown.

Oh my...the hottest Three little things that make this show spectacular...
One: That one note at the end of the "Shakedown" lead just before the final "bum bum bum..ba bum bada bum" shakes the earth. It's not even a guitar, just this sonic boom
Two: The "Estimated" lead. It's a friggin' anthem. One can imagine ancient Irish warriors racing into battle with the bagpipes playing this tune.
Three: "Eyes" is glorious in it's noodlely splendor. What the hell are those...1/164th notes?

Just my opinion...
This one is pretty sick! For a AUD from 78, this one kicks serious ass. A Neumann SM69 mic is a very high quality studio stereo microphone, and into a Nagra half track?!? Definitely worth the DL!
ugh The cut in the middle of Eyes is a real buzzkill!!!!

grateful birthday show What a great show to be played as I was brought into the world wow, loved the eyes usually like it faster like that and really I cant complain good birthday show, eyes being one of my favorite songs was nice to find out it was played on the day of my birth....Never get the dead outa my head like a whore outa bed :)

Sweet AUD! What a truly great sounding AUD.  

One hell of a job on the taping Greg.  

 I miss being at shows a lot:  Being able to hear AUDs like this sure helps though.

Thank you for sharing. 

5 stars on the recording.
